uations become critical. Other many-body approaches are critically\ncompared. It is argued that treating the spin fluctuations as if there was a\nMigdal's theorem can lead to wrong predictions, in particular with regard to\nthe the single-particle pseudogap.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Feb 1997 22:09:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 21 Feb 1997 01:50:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 11 Dec 1997 14:57:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-30"}
